column223: NEARBY SHIP DRONE CONTROL SYSTEM CAPACITY
column224: NEARBY SHIP DRONE CONTROL SYSTEM POWER
column225: NEARBY SHIP DRONE CONTROL SYSTEM DAMAGE
column284: HULL DAMAGE NEEDED FOR ESCAPE ATTEMPT

column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Asteroids -  Fighting in asteroid fields is dangerous, but use it to your advantage. Take out enemy Shields and let the rocks take care of the rest.

The nearby planet shows sign of habitation and great beauty. A rudimentary automated planetary defense system is looping its message into space: Warning! Quarantine Level 5 in effect under FHA Act 22, article 11.2. Warning! Quarantine Level 5...
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

There is only one other ship at this beacon, and it is showing heavy damage. You receive a message on your console: Greetings traveler. We were crippled by a band of pirates and are now forced to sell our remaining valuable equipment to acquire the necessary supplies to get home.
column12: System: drones, cloaking, battery, Drone: COMBAT BEAM 2, REPAIR, COMBAT 1, Augment: SHIELD RECHARGE, BATTERY BOOSTER, DRONE RECOVERY,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Despite your best efforts, the civilian ship breaks apart from the constant barrage. You are barely able to break out of the asteroid field yourself. The ship sustains some damage in the process.
The pirate's victim quickly jumps away before you have a chance to speak to them.

You locate the highest concentration of life forms and bring the ship alongside the station. Before you can begin to offload the survivors, a huge blast splits the station apart. Your ship is thrown away and some debris pierces your hull. You watch helplessly as the last of the survivors are consumed in the collapse of the station.
A brief exploration yields nothing of interest.
The outpost hails you after the scout was destroyed, Thanks for the help. We've been harassed non-stop by those scouts. Take this on the house.
The station is a storage site for military grade weapons. You find one that can be easily attached to the ship.
Thank you for your business.
The Rock people are a powerful and proud race. It is not unheard of to have a peaceful journey through their lands, but don't count on it.
You receive a message meant to degrade you as aliens. You half expect an attack but it seems to have come from a small civilian shuttle.
You find a pirate ship, damaged and abandoned. You salvage what you can and move on.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You receive a hail on Federation frequencies: You're Federation?! We- we weren't sure we'd ever see a friendly face again. There's little business here, perhaps you'd like to trade?
column12: Augment: WEAPON PREIGNITE, FTL JAMMER, BATTERY BOOSTER, System: teleporter, cloaking, hacking,

column11: A few freighters pass by but they refuse all communications. Must not want to sully their reputation by talking with foreigners.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Great. Take this bit of fuel as a down-payment. We'll be one step behind you, following your jump signatures. Don't want to take any risks now, do we? Added a quest marker to the next sector!
You salvage what you can from the ship. No one bothers you during the operation.
You take what you can and prepare to move on.
The war tore through this civilian sector, and just recently even the few life signs that remained have begun blinking out. Rumours suggest the Lanius are responsible.
You arrive and the ship you were escorting jumps in behind you. Thanks for the help. We work at a nearby fusion power plant, we could try to improve your reactor's output as a form of compensation.
He states that he was an infantryman before being stranded. He happily offers his services for a time in exchange for getting off that rock.

A large transport ship undergoing maintenance hails you. Greetings, friend. We're getting out of this sector as soon as this Coolant Shaft is fixed and I suggest you do the same. I half expect those damn metal freaks to come and try to melt down our ship at any moment. We're trying to offload some inventory - interested in buying something?
column12: System: drones, cloaking, battery, Drone: COMBAT BEAM, ANTI DRONE, DEFENSE 2, Augment: ION ARMOR, SCRAP COLLECTOR, FLEET DISTRACTION,

column11: It looks as if the Lanius were uninterested in the fuel reserves on the station, and there is a good amount of fuel left. You take what your ship can hold and prepare to jump to the next beacon.

The charts indicate this was the location of a small skirmish over a military facility on a nearby moon. Oddly, scans pick up no signs of debris from either the battle or the station. Yet another area sucked dry by the Lanius.
You arrive at an empty space station, no doubt abandoned due to the Lanius threat. Life signatures are detected at the ship depot and you spot a few crude signs stating Everything Must Go!
column12: Augment: HACKING STUN, FTL JAMMER, ION ARMOR, System: cloaking, clonebay, mind, Weapon: LASER BURST 2 A, BEAM HULL, BEAM 2, Crew: Slug, Engi, Slug,

column11: You stumble across a badly damaged Lanius craft. It jumps away as soon as it sees you. Looking around the area, you discover a number of destroyed Rebel automated ships. It must have been quite the fight. You scrap what remains.

An image of some weak and hungry humans comes onto your screen. Those metal bastards think they can just absorb half of our engines and leave us here to die? I hope you understand the need to take your ship by force. They must have a Super Shield bypass unit; boarders are on board!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
All around you is the stench of death and decay. The life sign readings must have been malfunctioning because you really doubt anything could be alive in here. You quickly return to the ship.
You arrive in Zoltan space. From what you have heard they anticipated the coming war and made preparations to hold their borders.
The Zoltan are fascinated by other species, and have set up something of an alien knick-knack shop here. Why not take a look?
column12: System: clonebay, mind, hacking, Crew: Zoltan, Zoltan, Human, Augment: BACKUP DNA, DRONE RECOVERY, FIRE EXTINGUISHERS,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Without active sensors you have no other option but to look out of the view-ports in apprehension. It's eerily quiet.
The ship obliterated, only scant fuel canisters can be scavenged from the wreckage before the ion storm clears and you have to jump away.
A Mantis crew here has hunkered down in the abdomen of a long-dead space-whale - the only way, presumably, for them to operate their black-market trade without detection. Worth a look?
column12: System: teleporter, cloaking, battery, Crew: Mantis, Slug, Slug,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

Your crew calmly lines up for the Zoltans to take their readings. After a short time, the process is done. They contact you, Thank you for your participation in our study. Please accept these small cakes made from stiff dough as well as some scrap.

The Zoltan hail once the smoke disperses. Thank you. We were led to believe Federation ideals died along with the Federation itself. Let us aid you a little, for old times' sake. You accept their reward and scrap, then collect some remains from the Rebel ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
A Zoltan shipyard is stationed at this beacon. You admire the display of hundreds of glowing Zoltan performing delicate exterior work on a massive transport ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Until you are able to jump away from the hostile space station, your sensors will be disabled. You should deal with these boarders first though!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Once the Federation forces were scattered, the Rebels came down hard on the locals here. Between the 'tax collectors' and military bases, the Rebel presence in this sector is high.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.

There appear to be a number of small stations nearby. Before you have time to scan them, warnings go off. A Rebel teleporter was used in one of the stations. You've been boarded! They must have a Super Shield bypass unit; boarders are on board!
Thank you, this will help greatly.
Automated refueling complete.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The station is a storage site for military grade weapons. You find one that can be easily attached to the ship.

You arrive near a small Rebel refueling depot. Your ship is being scanned multiple times so they must recognize you, but there appears to be no combat-ready ships in the vicinity. The only message you receive is a denial to your request to dock at the depot.
You arrive at a small space station that is putting out wide-band broadcasts on black-market channels. You doubt they would turn away any business, regardless of allegiances.
column12: System: drones, teleporter, clonebay, Drone: DEFENSE 1, COMBAT FIRE, SHIP REPAIR,

column11: Their ship breaks apart and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
You find a small cache of supplies that were surely left for any loyal Federation ships in trouble. You take all that you need, leaving some for others to find.
The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.

You dock with the station to take a look inside. However no sooner do you open the airlock than pirates burst in. Meanwhile multiple warning signals go off on the bridge. The pirates have activated a remote planetary defense system and it's locking onto your ship! They must have a Super Shield bypass unit; boarders are on board!
You have arrived in Engi space. The fall of the Federation has brought tough times for these robotic lifeforms, but they're usually willing to help.
A message arrives: Your scrap, ours. Our weapons for you. You're about to raise the shields when you realize it's just an Engi trader looking for a trade.
column12: Drone: DEFENSE 1, BOARDER, COMBAT BEAM, Crew: Engi, Human, Engi, Weapon: LASER HULL 1, BOMB FIRE, MISSILES 3, Augment: HACKING STUN, DEFENSE SCRAMBLER, DRONE RECOVERY,

column11: The Engi can do remarkable things with just a pile of scrap. The Engi hive at this beacon are selling equipment for just that.
column12: System: teleporter, cloaking, battery, Crew: Zoltan, Engi, Human, Augment: BACKUP DNA, SCRAP COLLECTOR, FTL BOOSTER, Weapon: LASER HEAVY 1, BEAM LONG, SHOTGUN,

column11: You use your beam to make a few precision cuts in the asteroid. The ship gives a quick burst of thrust and the rock crumbles away. They thank you and offer some of the resources they have collected.
Thank you for your business.
Thank you for your business, no refunds!
You find a pirate ship, damaged and abandoned. You salvage what you can and move on.
The station was in the process of being evacuated. A number of civilian Engi offer their gratitude as they finalize their preparations to leave. They offer some fuel as a reward.
You arrive at a green planet with great plains and rolling waterfalls. It would be of little interest to the Engi nearby.

This somewhat isolated region was thrown into chaos at the start of the rebellion. Even in peacetime it was always beset by pirates but now it houses a center of operations for countless pirate fleets.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

You receive a wide-band automated message, Welcome to our humble trade depot and shipyard! All are welcome, but try any funny business and our 152 automated turret satellites will tear your ship to shreds!
column12: System: teleporter, cloaking, mind, Crew: Engi, Mantis, Zoltan,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

Your ship detects a faint distress signal on a nearby moon. As you approach the rock, warning lights flash as hostiles beam aboard the ship from some hidden location. They must have a Super Shield bypass unit; boarders are on board!
With most of the fire under control, the scientists are able to help secure the station. They offer you their sincere gratitude and a generous reward.
With the pirates dissuaded from their career path, you return to the settlement. Thank you, they returned to us before you did. I don't think we'll need this anymore.
He states that he was an engineer before being stranded. He happily offers his services for a time in exchange for getting off that rock.

Your local radar flickers, periodically showing signs of a large object in the clouds nearby. However it's enough to get coordinates and you find the ship... an empty hull, long since stripped of functioning components.
Thank you for your business.
The pirate's victim quickly jumps away before you have a chance to speak to them.

Tully responds, It's settled. The Rebels will be here in a matter of moments. We will do what we can to hold off their warships but you must succeed in destroying this flagship. Your current outpost can provide some repairs and fuel, and the other repair stations can provide aid as well. Good luck.
You arrive to see a number of Federation forward-carriers and dreadnoughts. This must be a system of high importance to warrant such a fleet.

Human corpses are scattered across the station. You find the source of the signal, a lone survivor that locked themselves in a storage closet. You quickly retreat with them in tow back to the ship, and hope they can recover enough to be of some use.
A forward construction station is in the process of repairing damaged warships. Your command codes convince them to do a quick patch job on your ship.

You arrive near the Federation Base to find the bulk of their fleet skirmishing with Rebel forces. You hang back near the far side of the moon to avoid the conflict. There's not much you can do to help in that battle, and your mission holds the key to turn the tide of the war. You prepare to face the Flagship.
